4:
"It is to you, people, that I call;
\q my voice is for the sons of mankind.
\q

8:
All the words of my mouth are just;
\q in them is nothing twisted or misleading.
\q

10:
Acquire my instruction rather than silver;
\q acquire knowledge rather than pure gold.
\q

14:
I have good advice and sound wisdom;
\q I am insight; strength belongs to me.
\q

19:
My fruit is better than gold, even fine gold;
\q my produce is better than pure silver.
\q

33:
Listen to my instruction and be wise;
\q do not neglect it.
\q
